{
  "analysis": "The autotune process reached 100% and logged \"Training again with best arguments\", but no `/app/work/model_aut.bin` or `.ftz` was produced. Best validation F1 was only 0.5994, below the 0.62 target anyway. The terminal is back at the prompt. Before starting a new job, I need to confirm no fastText process is still running (to avoid resource contention), clean up failed autotune artifacts, and then train one manual model with character n-grams, which should improve accuracy over the previous word-level models. I will use moderate parameters to keep the model manageable and quantize later if needed. I will poll cleanly without concatenating commands.",
  "plan": "1. Check for any running fastText process by inspecting `/proc/*/comm` since `ps` is unavailable; also check the autotune PID.\n2. Clean up autotune artifacts and prepare for manual training.\n3. Verify the prepared data files exist with expected line counts.\n4. Start one background fastText training job with character n-grams (`minn 3`, `maxn 5`), `wordNgrams 2`, `dim 100`, `epoch 20`, `lr 0.6`, `bucket 200000`, `minCount 2`, softmax loss, on `/app/work/train.txt`.\n5. Poll for up to about 5.5 minutes to monitor progress/ETA. Later batches will wait/evaluate/quantize/save the final model.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "pid=$(cat /app/work/autotune.pid 2>/dev/null || true); if [ -n \"$pid\" ] && [ -d \"/proc/$pid\" ]; then echo \"autotune status=running pid=$pid\"; else echo \"autotune status=finished pid=$pid\"; fi\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -l 'fasttext' /proc/*/comm 2>/dev/null | while read p; do echo \"$p: $(cat \"$p\" 2>/dev/null)\"; done | head -40 || echo 'no fasttext procs via comm'\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "rm -f /app/work/model_aut.bin /app/work/model_aut.ftz /app/work/model_aut.vec /app/work/autotune.log /app/work/autotune.pid /app/work/model_char.bin /app/work/model_char.vec /app/work/model_char.ftz /app/work/train_char.log /app/work/train_char.pid\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "wc -l /app/work/train.txt /app/work/test.txt\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup /opt/fastText/fasttext supervised -input /app/work/train.txt -output /app/work/model_char -dim 100 -epoch 20 -lr 0.6 -wordNgrams 2 -minn 3 -maxn 5 -bucket 200000 -minCount 2 -loss softmax -thread $(nproc) > /app/work/train_char.log 2>&1 &\necho $! > /app/work/train_char.pid\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "for i in $(seq 1 10); do\n  pid=$(cat /app/work/train_char.pid 2>/dev/null || true)\n  if [ -n \"$pid\" ] && [ -d \"/proc/$pid\" ]; then status=running; else status=finished; fi\n  size=$(stat -c %s /app/work/model_char.bin 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n  printf 'iter=%s status=%s bin_size=%s ' \"$i\" \"$status\" \"$size\"\n  tail -1 /app/work/train_char.log 2>/dev/null || true\n  if [ \"$status\" = finished ] && [ \"$size\" -gt 0 ]; then echo 'training_done_break'; break; fi\n  sleep 30\ndone\n",
      "duration": 330.0
    }
  ]
}
